      "note_no": "49",
      "note": "Evidently, the King wanted to find out whether they had previously been encouraged by Joseph, or whether he was truly innocent. The noun khatb denotes \"something that one has in view\" or \"desires\" or \"seeks to obtain\"; and so the expression and khatbukunna (lit., \"what was it that you [really] had in view\") may be suitably rendered as above."
